Package data.reader

Interface RelationStreamReader<T,Q>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the Keys in use in the relation.
    Q - The type of the Values in use in the relation.

    public interface RelationStreamReader<T,Q>
    An interface for Reading and providing values from .rel files.

    .rel files contain the system Check relational data e.g Domain gives Subdomain, Subdomain gives Check and Check gives Implementation.

    Author:
    Jack Coffey

      • getKeys

        T[] getKeys​()
        A relation is compromised of Keys and Values.

        Many times it's important to know the possible Keys of a Relation, in order to iterate through the values.

        Returns:
        An exhaustive array of type T of all T keys in this .rel file.

      • getValue

        Q getValue​(T key)
        A relation is compromised of Keys and Values.

        Keys give Values, in other words we can get a Value by providing the Key that the value is relationally linked to.

        Parameters:
        key - A T type key used to identify values.
        Returns:
        A Q type Value relationally linked to the provided Key.
